description: {"blocks":[{"key":"5dnoe","text":"Removal of excess dideoxy terminators from the sequencing mix after the enzymatic reaction is a key process affecting the dideoxy/Sanger sequencing quality. Ethanol precipitation may be the most popular clean-up method because of its low costs; however, it takes a long centrifugation time and frequently results in low quality sequence data. Commercially available clean-up kits provide high quality sequence data, while they generally have high cost. Here, we describe rapid, effective and low-cost dideoxy terminator clean-up method using a home-made magnetic beads suspension, MagNA, and magnetic separator. We found that MagNA enables rapid and efficient clean-up at ~1/100 of the cost of commercially available kits. The magnetic separator made using low-cost neodymium magnets worked well for the MagNA separation, representing a the rapid, efficient and cost-effective dideoxy terminator clean-up system.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"7cvai","text":"Prepare 50 ml buffer without magnet beads as follow. Final concentration of each chemical is indicated in parenthesis. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9d98c","text":"Dissolve 9 g PEG 8,000 (18 %), 2.92 g NaCl (1 M), 5 ml 10x TE (1x), 25 µl Tween-20 (0.05 %) and 50 µl ProClin 300 (0.1 %) in DW to prepare 50 ml PEG-NaCl buffer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"871om","text":"Mix thoroughly Carboxyl-modified Sera-Mag Magnetic Speed-beads (Hydrophobic) (Cytiva, cat. #65152105050250), take 1 ml Sera-Mag suspension and separate the beads by using magnetic separator. Add 1 ml 1x TE, mix, stand on magnetic separator, and remove the supernatant. Repeat this wash once.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2rp4f","text":"Add 1 ml PEG-NaCl buffer, mix and transfer the suspension to the PEG-NaCl buffer tube to prepare MagNA suspension. Store at 4 °C at least for one year.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ap0tr","text":"Set pairs of magnets at the edge of the insert by their magnetic force as they line to tip halls (Fig. 1b and c).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clean-up of dideoxy sequencing reaction by MagNA and home-made magnetic separator
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"33pdv","text":"The procedure is based on the protocol of CleanSeq (Beckman Coulter) as below.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clean-up of dideoxy sequencing reaction by MagNA and home-made magnetic separator
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6do1p","text":"Shake MagNA to fully resuspend the magnetic beads.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clean-up of dideoxy sequencing reaction by MagNA and home-made magnetic separator
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1t7h5","text":"To the 10 µl sequencing reaction, add 10 µl MagNA suspension.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clean-up of dideoxy sequencing reaction by MagNA and home-made magnetic separator
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"b4k3i","text":"Add 42 µl 85 % EtOH (Volume of 85% Ethanol = 2.077  (10 L + Sequencing Sample Volume) and mix thoroughly.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clean-up of dideoxy sequencing reaction by MagNA and home-made magnetic separator
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"fr2t4","text":"Place the tube in the home-made magnetic separator for 2~3 min (Fig. 1d).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clean-up of dideoxy sequencing reaction by MagNA and home-made magnetic separator
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"93ter","text":"Remove the supernatant, add 100 µl of 85 % ethanol, and remove the supernatant after \u003e30 sec. Repeat the step once.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clean-up of dideoxy sequencing reaction by MagNA and home-made magnetic separator
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"d0pr","text":"Remove the tube from the separator, and add 40 µl DW.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Clean-up of dideoxy sequencing reaction by MagNA and home-made magnetic separator
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"182lq","text":"Place the tube in the home-made magnetic separator for 2~3 min, recover 35 µl of supernatant and subject it for sequencing.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
